      • KerasModel

        protected KerasModel(java.lang.String modelJson,
                     java.lang.String modelYaml,
                     Hdf5Archive weightsArchive,

                     java.lang.String trainingJson,
                     Hdf5Archive trainingArchive,
                     boolean enforceTrainingConfig,
                     int[] inputShape,
                     KerasLayer.DimOrder dimOrder)
              throws java.io.IOException,
                     InvalidKerasConfigurationException,
                     UnsupportedKerasConfigurationException
        (Not recommended) Constructor for (Functional API) Model from model configuration (JSON or YAML), training configuration (JSON), weights, and "training mode" boolean indicator. When built in training mode, certain unsupported configurations (e.g., unknown regularizers) will throw Exceptions. When enforceTrainingConfig=false, these will generate warnings but will be otherwise ignored.
        Parameters:
        modelJson - model configuration JSON string
        modelYaml - model configuration YAML string
        enforceTrainingConfig - whether to enforce training-related configurations
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IO exception
        InvalidKerasConfigurationException - Invalid Keras config
        UnsupportedKerasConfigurationException - Unsupported Keras config
